1
00:00:11,290 --> 00:00:20,990


2
00:00:36,010 --> 00:00:41,680
♫  No matter if it's a rainy day or a sunny day  ♫

3
00:00:41,680 --> 00:00:47,120
♫  As long as you are by my side  ♫ 
 ♫  Even the sunlight becomes dazzling  ♫

4
00:00:47,120 --> 00:00:52,830
♫  Thinking too much, blindly guessing  ♫ 
 ♫  Why not find a day to meet  ♫

5
00:00:52,830 --> 00:00:59,260
♫  Saying too much, there's no "what if"  ♫ 
 ♫  Might as well go on an adventure  ♫

6
00:00:59,260 --> 00:01:02,780
♫  I stand in the shadows  ♫

7
00:01:02,780 --> 00:01:08,120
♫  Reaching out, waiting for your rescue  ♫

8
00:01:08,120 --> 00:01:13,070
♫  Between you and me  ♫ 
 ♫  Even if the world collapses  ♫

9
00:01:13,070 --> 00:01:17,160
♫  No matter how far the distance  ♫

10
00:01:17,160 --> 00:01:21,620
♫  Nothing can stop our meeting  ♫

11
00:01:21,620 --> 00:01:28,610
♫  Stepping through the long dark night  ♫ 
 ♫  You are standing at the finish line  ♫

12
00:01:28,610 --> 00:01:32,820
♫  Protecting you is my tiny wish  ♫

13
00:01:32,820 --> 00:01:37,270
♫  Goodbye to the shy me of the past  ♫

14
00:01:37,270 --> 00:01:42,550
♫  Because of you, I have become a little braver  ♫

15
00:01:42,550 --> 00:01:46,380
   

16
00:01:46,380 --> 00:01:49,180
   
   

17
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:54,740
Liu Yuan!

18
00:01:54,740 --> 00:01:58,480
You said the exam was legit, but I didn't get a single question right. Explain yourself!

19
00:01:58,480 --> 00:02:00,600
Buddy, you've got it wrong.

20
00:02:00,600 --> 00:02:03,320
How could I get the real questions?

21
00:02:03,320 --> 00:02:06,134
What I sold you were mock questions I compiled

22
00:02:06,134 --> 00:02:08,380
from previous years' Advanced Mathematics exams.

23
00:02:08,380 --> 00:02:10,460
I spent 500 yuan on your mock questions?

24
00:02:10,460 --> 00:02:12,000
Who's crazy here?

25
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:14,580
Buddy, show me proof.

26
00:02:14,580 --> 00:02:16,620
Don't make unfounded accusations.

27
00:02:16,620 --> 00:02:21,141
Even so, if I sold the real questions, it would be cheating.

28
00:02:21,141 --> 00:02:25,600
You should've reported me to the dean's office instead of buying exam questions from me.

29
00:02:27,620 --> 00:02:29,260
- Forget it. 
 - You fraud. Come down!

30
00:02:29,260 --> 00:02:30,680
Forget it!

31
00:02:30,680 --> 00:02:32,860
Don't argue with him. Forget it. Let's go.

32
00:02:32,860 --> 00:02:35,540
- Come down! 
 - Stop it. Calm down.

33
00:02:35,540 --> 00:02:36,840
- You scammer! 
 - Go.

34
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:38,640
Enough.

35
00:02:39,260 --> 00:02:40,780
   

36
00:02:40,780 --> 00:02:42,090
Why did you stop me just now?

37
00:02:42,090 --> 00:02:45,240
I should've beaten him black and blue and taught him a lesson.

38
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:46,610
Just save your energy.

39
00:02:46,610 --> 00:02:50,280
You should take this as a lesson. Just don't do it again.

40
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:52,120
No. I can't swallow this.

41
00:02:52,120 --> 00:02:54,680
Come back.

42
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:58,000
Think about it. If you beat him up, not only will you not get your money back,

43
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:59,260
you'll also have to pay his medical bills.

44
00:02:59,260 --> 00:03:03,440
People like him will blackmail you. You'll suffer.

45
00:03:03,440 --> 00:03:05,520
Jeez.

46
00:03:05,520 --> 00:03:06,930
Jing is right.

47
00:03:06,930 --> 00:03:09,400
You should endure it and let things calm down.

48
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:11,550
I understand.

49
00:03:11,550 --> 00:03:14,650
Endure it? The more I think about it, the angrier I get.

50
00:03:14,650 --> 00:03:17,000
Anger will hurt your liver, young man.

51
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:19,490
No. It's easy for you to say.

52
00:03:19,490 --> 00:03:20,720
You're not the one who lost 500 yuan.

53
00:03:20,720 --> 00:03:23,240
You know how many eggs I could've bought?

54
00:03:24,590 --> 00:03:27,480
No! I want to beat him!

55
00:03:29,910 --> 00:03:31,090
Don't stop me!

56
00:03:31,090 --> 00:03:32,890
I'm going to beat him!

57
00:03:32,890 --> 00:03:35,820
- Calm down! 
 - Put me down!

58
00:03:36,540 --> 00:03:40,720
 The first semester of freshman year ended just like that. 

59
00:03:41,340 --> 00:03:44,120
 Our Top Student got first place again as she wished. 

60
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:46,000
   

61
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:51,340
 Zhou Ye spent 500 yuan and still failed the exam. 

62
00:03:51,340 --> 00:03:53,240
 As for Huang Lu and Qiu Li... 
   

63
00:03:53,240 --> 00:03:56,440
 One scored 56, the other scored 59. 

64
00:03:56,440 --> 00:04:00,820
 Obviously, Qiu Li who scored 59 was angrier than Huang Lu. 

65
00:04:00,820 --> 00:04:02,070
How come you scored more than me?

66
00:04:02,070 --> 00:04:04,560
Aren't I still one mark short?

67
00:04:09,190 --> 00:04:10,650
Hello, Sir.

68
00:04:10,650 --> 00:04:15,440
Could you help me check and see if you miscalculated?

69
00:04:17,510 --> 00:04:20,290
 As for me, I didn't do too badly. 

70
00:04:20,290 --> 00:04:21,850
 My score is 76. 

71
00:04:21,850 --> 00:04:25,010
 There's still a lot of room for improvement. 

72
00:04:28,280 --> 00:04:30,460
 What I didn't expect was that Jing Xi Chi, 

73
00:04:30,460 --> 00:04:33,680
 who was at the bottom of the class in high school, 

74
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:36,460
 got full marks in Advanced Mathematics. 

75
00:04:36,460 --> 00:04:38,730
 But no matter how we did in the exam, 

76
00:04:38,730 --> 00:04:42,640
 these are already preludes in the river of time. 

77
00:04:42,640 --> 00:04:49,010
 As for those unfinished stories, let's wait until next semester. 

78
00:04:58,258 --> 00:05:00,240
   

79
00:05:00,240 --> 00:05:01,560
Enough.

80
00:05:01,560 --> 00:05:03,560
Stop looking at it.

81
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:07,370
We'll only know if it's benign or malignant after the biopsy.

82
00:05:07,370 --> 00:05:08,850
What's a biopsy?

83
00:05:08,850 --> 00:05:12,080
A biopsy means cutting it out for an examination.

84
00:05:12,080 --> 00:05:13,850
Then hurry up and do it. What are you waiting for?

85
00:05:13,850 --> 00:05:15,940
Do you think it's as easy as cutting vegetables?

86
00:05:15,940 --> 00:05:17,288
You have to make an appointment.

87
00:05:17,288 --> 00:05:18,700
So have you made an appointment?

88
00:05:18,700 --> 00:05:20,320
Yes.

89
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:22,440
Take it easy. I'm a doctor.

90
00:05:22,440 --> 00:05:24,880
- I know what to do. 
 - You make it sound so simple.

91
00:05:24,880 --> 00:05:26,610
How could I not be nervous?

92
00:05:26,610 --> 00:05:29,130
You should swallow that fear right back down.

93
00:05:29,910 --> 00:05:31,000
Don't let Huan Er know.

94
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:33,850
She will be back soon. Hurry and put it away.

95
00:05:33,850 --> 00:05:36,200
So many dishes still to cook.

96
00:05:36,200 --> 00:05:37,530
- Hurry! 
 - Mom.

97
00:05:37,530 --> 00:05:39,560
- Put it away. 
 - I'm back!

98
00:05:39,560 --> 00:05:41,240
Coming!

99
00:05:42,030 --> 00:05:43,050
My daughter is back.

100
00:05:43,050 --> 00:05:46,240
- Mom! 
 - Darling, you're back.

101
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:47,490
My little dumpling!

102
00:05:47,490 --> 00:05:50,080
- Let me see if you've gained weight. 
 - Your dad has been waiting.

103
00:05:50,080 --> 00:05:51,380
One, two, three.

104
00:05:51,380 --> 00:05:52,810
- She's like a piglet. 
 - Put her down.

105
00:05:52,810 --> 00:05:55,640
- You're old now. Watch your waist! 
 - Not bad. Looks like you've put on some weight.

106
00:05:55,640 --> 00:05:56,930
- Did I gain weight? 
 - No.

107
00:05:56,930 --> 00:05:57,930
Hurry. Sit.

108
00:05:57,930 --> 00:06:01,530
I almost forgot... Dad, Mom, I have a surprise for you.

109
00:06:01,530 --> 00:06:02,850
You brought us gifts?

110
00:06:02,850 --> 00:06:05,410
- Yes. 
 - Did you buy our gifts with our money?

111
00:06:05,410 --> 00:06:07,610
- Jeez. 
 - Here. I prepared it myself.

112
00:06:07,610 --> 00:06:10,050
- Really? 
 - Let me see.

113
00:06:10,050 --> 00:06:13,800
Gosh. Look at this. Look who she took after.

114
00:06:16,510 --> 00:06:18,630
- Oh no. 
 - No, Chen Huan Er.

115
00:06:18,630 --> 00:06:19,780
What are you doing?

116
00:06:19,780 --> 00:06:23,050
You have to tighten these bottles before putting them in.

117
00:06:23,050 --> 00:06:24,610
You just put everything in.

118
00:06:24,610 --> 00:06:25,640
Now I know.

119
00:06:25,640 --> 00:06:28,170
It's my fault for not teaching you basic life skills.

120
00:06:28,170 --> 00:06:29,680
- Enough. 
 - What will you do without me?

121
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:31,710
- I knitted the scarves myself. 
 - Stop nagging.

122
00:06:31,710 --> 00:06:33,510
Enough. It's a token of her sincerity.

123
00:06:33,510 --> 00:06:36,590
I knitted this red one for you.

124
00:06:36,590 --> 00:06:38,220
The blue one is for Dad.

125
00:06:38,220 --> 00:06:39,300
Sure.

126
00:06:39,300 --> 00:06:41,860
There are only a few stitches left. I'll finish them soon.

127
00:06:41,860 --> 00:06:43,910
It's fragrant. How nice.

128
00:06:43,910 --> 00:06:45,150
Do you like it, Mom?

129
00:06:45,150 --> 00:06:47,910
This color is not bad.

130
00:06:47,910 --> 00:06:51,300
The stitching is not bad either.

131
00:06:51,300 --> 00:06:53,180
You're talented.

132
00:06:53,180 --> 00:06:54,740
- My classmate taught me. 
 - Good.

133
00:06:54,740 --> 00:06:56,860
Honey, hurry and wash it for me.

134
00:06:56,860 --> 00:06:58,830
I don't need to buy a scarf this year.

135
00:06:58,830 --> 00:06:59,810
- Okay. 
 - Wash it clean.

136
00:06:59,810 --> 00:07:01,660
- Do you like it? 
 - Okay.

137
00:07:01,660 --> 00:07:02,830
My daughter did a good job.

138
00:07:02,830 --> 00:07:05,880
Come and sit down. I have something for you.

139
00:07:07,220 --> 00:07:08,830
How comfortable.

140
00:07:08,830 --> 00:07:09,950
Mom.

141
00:07:09,950 --> 00:07:11,830
I want beef with celery today.

142
00:07:11,830 --> 00:07:14,180
Your favorite stir-fried beef with celery.

143
00:07:14,180 --> 00:07:15,780
Here.

144
00:07:15,780 --> 00:07:17,000
Sign this.

145
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:18,540
Insurance? 
    

146
00:07:18,540 --> 00:07:21,390
Why did you suddenly buy insurance?

147
00:07:21,390 --> 00:07:24,160
I thought it was suitable and bought it for you.

148
00:07:24,160 --> 00:07:26,720
You'll be insured and won't suffer any loss.

149
00:07:27,180 --> 00:07:30,660
Besides, you're a grown-up girl.

150
00:07:30,660 --> 00:07:33,040
Huan Er, you've grown up.

151
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:35,510
You need to learn to take care of yourself.

152
00:07:35,510 --> 00:07:37,470
I can't stay by your side forever.

153
00:07:37,470 --> 00:07:41,950
No. I want to be with you forever. I don't care.

154
00:07:41,950 --> 00:07:44,510
Enough. Hurry and put those things away.

155
00:07:44,510 --> 00:07:47,620
Later, Song Cong, Xi Chi and their families will be here for a meal.

156
00:07:47,620 --> 00:07:49,710
- Look at you. 
 - When will they be here?

157
00:07:49,710 --> 00:07:51,180
Soon.

158
00:07:51,180 --> 00:07:53,640
I don't care. Put it away yourself.

159
00:07:55,830 --> 00:07:58,340
Mom, I'll put it in the bathroom first.

160
00:08:20,410 --> 00:08:22,510
How dare you come back?

161
00:08:31,940 --> 00:08:34,460
Why did you change your major?

162
00:08:36,110 --> 00:08:38,340
Many people try very hard to get into

163
00:08:38,340 --> 00:08:41,150
the law program at University of Political Science and Law.

164
00:08:41,150 --> 00:08:42,680
Look at you!

165
00:08:42,680 --> 00:08:44,990
You changed to some literature?

166
00:08:44,990 --> 00:08:47,872
I'm just trying to do what I want.

167
00:08:47,872 --> 00:08:52,390
You're using your family's money to do what you want.

168
00:08:54,820 --> 00:08:57,210
What an easy life.

169
00:08:58,800 --> 00:09:01,133
You don't have to use money to pressure me.

170
00:09:01,133 --> 00:09:04,160
I know that parents have no obligation to support their adult children.

171
00:09:04,160 --> 00:09:07,650
I'll find a way to pay for my future tuition. You don't have to worry.

172
00:09:07,650 --> 00:09:09,750
I'm an adult now.

173
00:09:09,750 --> 00:09:12,460
You're no longer my guardian.

174
00:09:13,520 --> 00:09:16,180
You've grown capable since going to university.

175
00:09:16,180 --> 00:09:20,090
Sure. Since you're talking to me about the law, let me tell you

176
00:09:20,090 --> 00:09:24,260
that adult children have a lifetime obligation to support their parents.

177
00:09:25,030 --> 00:09:29,150
As long as I live, you'll always be my daughter.

178
00:09:29,150 --> 00:09:32,510
You can never repay what you owe me.

179
00:09:32,510 --> 00:09:34,280
Okay.

180
00:09:34,280 --> 00:09:36,246
Go ahead and sue me, Ms. Qi.

181
00:09:36,246 --> 00:09:38,630
I'll repay you whatever amount the court sentences me.

182
00:09:38,630 --> 00:09:41,210
By then, we'll be completely even.

183
00:09:53,840 --> 00:09:55,130
 Be careful. Don't burn yourself. 

184
00:09:55,130 --> 00:09:57,720
- Here. Be careful. 
 - Be careful, Mom.

185
00:09:57,720 --> 00:09:58,820
It's hot, Mom.

186
00:09:58,820 --> 00:10:00,820
Amazing. You cooked so much.

187
00:10:00,820 --> 00:10:02,540
Here. Here.

188
00:10:02,540 --> 00:10:04,320
- Here, you can start. 
 - You can do it.

189
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:11,280
Our three families are having a pre‑New Year's dinner tonight.

190
00:10:11,280 --> 00:10:12,670
I'll propose a toast.

191
00:10:12,670 --> 00:10:18,120
Congratulations to each of us, for spending another year safely.

192
00:10:18,120 --> 00:10:19,170
Happy New Year!

193
00:10:19,170 --> 00:10:22,160
- Happy New Year! 
 - Happy New Year!

194
00:10:23,480 --> 00:10:24,990
Li Na, you're awesome.

195
00:10:24,990 --> 00:10:27,180
You made so much food.

196
00:10:27,180 --> 00:10:29,030
Good job. Your cooking has improved.

197
00:10:29,030 --> 00:10:32,350
All right. Our cooking is far inferior to Hao Mei's.

198
00:10:32,350 --> 00:10:34,660
- Yes. 
 - Kids. Don't be picky.

199
00:10:34,660 --> 00:10:36,860
- Just enjoy. 
 - Sure.

200
00:10:36,860 --> 00:10:38,940
But when is your husband coming?

201
00:10:38,940 --> 00:10:42,000
Don't even mention it. Got a call from the hospital this afternoon and rushed off again.

202
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:43,930
I told him we'd have dinner together and come early.

203
00:10:43,930 --> 00:10:46,180
- Or he would have to wash the pots. 
 - That's right.

204
00:10:46,180 --> 00:10:47,910
Ask him to hurry up.

205
00:10:47,910 --> 00:10:49,700
Speak of the devil. He's here.

206
00:10:49,700 --> 00:10:50,990
Not bad. He's fast.

207
00:10:50,990 --> 00:10:52,090
Not bad. Look at him.

208
00:10:52,090 --> 00:10:53,480
 - Yeah. 
 - He made it in time. 

209
00:10:53,480 --> 00:10:56,240
 - He knows we have delicious food today. 
 - That's right. 

210
00:10:56,890 --> 00:10:58,170
Qi Qi?

211
00:10:58,170 --> 00:10:59,380
Why are you here?

212
00:10:59,380 --> 00:11:01,760
Huan Er, I had a fight with my mom.

213
00:11:01,760 --> 00:11:03,720
Can I stay at your house for a few days?

214
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:05,640
What happened?

215
00:11:06,360 --> 00:11:08,390
I'll tell you later.

216
00:11:08,390 --> 00:11:10,990
Hurry. Hurry inside.

217
00:11:10,990 --> 00:11:14,110
Mom, Qi Qi came to visit us today.

218
00:11:14,110 --> 00:11:16,160
Well... Hello, everyone. Sorry for bothering you.

219
00:11:16,160 --> 00:11:18,810
Qi Qi's here. Sit here.

220
00:11:18,810 --> 00:11:20,870
- Huan Er, get a pair of chopsticks. 
 - Okay.

221
00:11:20,870 --> 00:11:22,050
- Get a set of tableware. 
 - Okay.

222
00:11:22,050 --> 00:11:24,300
- Sorry for bothering you. 
 - No. It's fine.

223
00:11:24,300 --> 00:11:28,420
Look, all those high schoolers are now university students.

224
00:11:28,420 --> 00:11:31,120
- Not bad, right? 
 - Huan Er, have you grown taller?

225
00:11:31,120 --> 00:11:32,230
- Right? 
 - She did.

226
00:11:32,230 --> 00:11:33,480
She seems to have grown taller.

227
00:11:33,480 --> 00:11:36,720
Did she? Why do I feel like she's shorter than when I first met her?

228
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:38,280
Who's short? Get up. Let's compare.

229
00:11:38,280 --> 00:11:39,800
- Have I grown taller? 
 - Enough.

230
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:42,420
- Have I grown taller? 
 - Who's taller?

231
00:11:42,420 --> 00:11:45,080
- I've grown taller! 
 - Hurry up. Come over and eat.

232
00:11:45,080 --> 00:11:46,530
You two argue every day.

233
00:11:46,530 --> 00:11:48,030
Troublemakers.

234
00:11:48,030 --> 00:11:49,110
Li Na.

235
00:11:49,110 --> 00:11:53,870
I think Huan Er would be a good match for Xi Chi.

236
00:11:53,870 --> 00:11:54,960
Yi Fan.

237
00:11:54,960 --> 00:11:56,800
Show some decency.

238
00:11:56,800 --> 00:11:58,180
I had my eye on Chen Huan Er first.

239
00:11:58,180 --> 00:12:01,320
She's my daughter-in-law. You can't steal her from me.

240
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:04,276
Your son is handsome and capable.

241
00:12:04,276 --> 00:12:05,400
He'll find a girlfriend.

242
00:12:05,400 --> 00:12:06,820
- Yeah. 
 - Xi Chi is incapable.

243
00:12:06,820 --> 00:12:08,250
Look at that silly kid.

244
00:12:08,250 --> 00:12:10,870
He's indeed handsome. I won't argue with you on this.

245
00:12:10,870 --> 00:12:13,680
But his personality and temper are just like his dad's.

246
00:12:13,680 --> 00:12:14,820
Too inarticulate.

247
00:12:14,820 --> 00:12:19,160
He's unlike Xi Chi, who's good-natured and clever.

248
00:12:19,160 --> 00:12:21,640
My son is incapable. That's why...

249
00:12:21,640 --> 00:12:23,630
That's not what you said.

250
00:12:23,630 --> 00:12:25,520
How could you two say that?

251
00:12:25,520 --> 00:12:27,840
Even I can't stand it anymore. Seriously.

252
00:12:27,840 --> 00:12:29,154
- Yeah. 
 - Are you saying that Huan Er

253
00:12:29,154 --> 00:12:31,510
- can only pick what's left? 
 - That's not what I meant.

